aws::graph::propositions: Aircraft Information for Bombardier CL600 2D24-900 N943LR
Bombardier is an aircraft manufacturer.
The aircraft model is CL600 2D24-900.
The aircraft was manufactured in 2006.
The aircraft has a Transport airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft has a retractable tricycle landing gear.
The aircraft's last inspection was on June 26, 2014.
The aircraft's last inspection was a continuous airworthiness inspection.
The aircraft had 12283 hours at the time of the accident.
The aircraft has a C126 Emergency Locator Transmitter installed.
The C126 Emergency Locator Transmitter was not activated.
The registered owner of the aircraft is MESA AIRLINES INC.
The operator of the aircraft is MESA AIRLINES INC.
MESA AIRLINES INC does business as American Eagle.
The aircraft registration is N943LR.
The aircraft category is Airplane.
The aircraft serial number is 15068.
The aircraft has 80 seats.
The aircraft's certified maximum gross weight is 82060 pounds.
The aircraft has 2 turbo fan engines.
The engine manufacturer is General Electric.
The engine model is CF34-8C5.
The engines are rated at 14500 pounds of thrust.
MESA AIRLINES INC holds Flag carrier (121) operating certificate.
MESA AIRLINES INC holds Supplemental operating certificate.
The operator designator code for MESA AIRLINES INC is SIMA.
